CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778681476
OL,3,CUS author's children 'so scared' of
OL,4,Cher release after she killed her
OL,5,Chusband
OL,7,FPrison time for the attempted
OL,8,Faggravated murder charge depends on
OL,9,Fthe severity of the bodily injury that
OL,10,Foccurred.
OL,12,FAfter taking a bite of the sandwich
OL,13,Fhis wife left for him, Eric Richins
OL,14,Fbroke out in hives, injected himself
OL,15,Fwith his son's EpiPen, drank a bottle
OL,16,Fof Benadryl and passed out,
OL,17,Fprosecutors said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778681476
OL,3,CUS author's children 'so scared' of
OL,4,Cher release after she killed her
OL,5,Chusband
OL,7,FDepending on the judge's assessment,
OL,8,FKouri Richins could face 15 years to
OL,9,Flife, 6 years to life or 5 years to
OL,10,Flife for that charge.
OL,12,FTwo counts of insurance fraud, second-
OL,13,Fdegree felonies, each carry a 1-15
OL,14,Fyear sentence, and a third-degree
OL,15,Ffelony forgery charge is punishable by
OL,16,F0-5 years in prison.
OL,18,FRichins also faces more than two dozen
OL,19,Fmoney-related criminal charges in a
OL,20,Fseparate case that has not yet gone to
OL,21,Ftrial.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778681476
OL,3,CUS author's children 'so scared' of
OL,4,Cher release after she killed her
OL,5,Chusband
OL,7,FThe trial was shorter than expected
OL,8,Fafter Richins refused to testify and
OL,9,Fher defence team chose not to call any
OL,10,Fwitnesses.
OL,12,FHer lawyers said they were confident
OL,13,Fthat prosecutors had not produced
OL,14,Fenough evidence to convict her of
OL,15,Fmurder.
OL,17,FThe jury deliberated for just under
OL,18,Fthree hours before finding her guilty
OL,19,Fof all counts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
